<topic template="Default" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../helpproject.xsd">
  <title translate="true">Accessing MVP Views and Presenters</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword translate="true">Accessing MVP Views and Presenters</keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Accessing MVP Views and Presenters</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="body-text" style="text-align:left; text-indent:0px; margin-top:9px; margin-right:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; line-height:1.46; background-color:transparent; white-space:normal; page-break-inside:auto; page-break-after:auto; border:none; tabstops:none;"><text styleclass="body-text" style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; text-decoration:none; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#000000; background-color:transparent; letter-spacing:normal; letter-scaling:100%;" translate="true">The context menu for the </text><text style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic; color:#000000;" translate="true">Classes</text><text styleclass="body-text" style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; text-decoration:none; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#000000; background-color:transparent; letter-spacing:normal; letter-scaling:100%;" translate="true"> pane offers some additional commands for classes that are </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="glossmvp" style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; color:#000000;" translate="true">MVP</link><text style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; color:#000000;" translate="true"> views or presenters.</text></para>
    <list id="1" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" style="text-indent:-13px; margin-left:39px; font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; color:#000000;">
      <li style="text-indent:-13px; margin-left:39px;"><text style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; color:#000000;" translate="true">The </text><text style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic; color:#000000;" translate="true">View/Edit </text><text style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; color:#000000;" translate="true">pull-out</text><text style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic; color:#000000;" translate="true">&#32;</text><text style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; color:#000000;" translate="true">menu</text><text style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic; color:#000000;" translate="true">&#32;</text><text style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; color:#000000;" translate="true">allows you to choose from a list of the existing </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="glossresources" style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; color:#000000;" translate="true">resources</link><text style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; color:#000000;" translate="true"> before opening the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="glossviewcomposer" style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; color:#000000;" translate="true">View Composer</link><text style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; color:#000000;" translate="true"> onto the one you select. Note that if there is only one view resource for the class then the View Composer will be opened directly on it.</text></li>
      <li style="text-indent:-13px; margin-left:39px;"><text style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; color:#000000;" translate="true">The </text><text style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic; color:#000000;" translate="true">View/Show </text><text style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; color:#000000;" translate="true">pull-out menu allows you to choose from a list of the existing view resources for the class. It will then attempt to show the class within the chosen view.</text></li>
      <li style="text-indent:-13px; margin-left:39px;"><text style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; color:#000000;" translate="true">The </text><text style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic; color:#000000;" translate="true">View/New </text><text style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; color:#000000;" translate="true">command will create a new copy of an appropriate default view for the chosen class and will open the View Composer onto this. In this case, the resource to be copied is identified by the #</text><text style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic; color:#000000;" translate="true">defaultView</text><text style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; color:#000000;" translate="true"> class method of the class.</text></li>
    </list>
  </body>
